016 |accessdate=10 February 2016 |author=Blistein, Jon |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160210093249/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/taylor-swift-the-weeknd-lead-iheartradio-music-awards-noms-20160209 |archivedate=10 February 2016}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.iheart.com/features/iheartradio-music-awards-15/articles/15/490103/surprise-announcement-adele-accepts-song-of-14552999/ |title=Surprise Announcement! Adele Accepts Song Of The Year iHeartRadio Music Award In The Middle Of Her Concert |publisher=[[iHeartMedia]] |date=31 March 2016 |accessdate=31 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406072716/http://news.iheart.com/features/iheartradio-music-awards-15/articles/15/490103/surprise-announcement-adele-accepts-song-of-14552999/ |archivedate=6 April 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| Song of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Juno Awards]]\n| [[Juno Award for Video of the Year| Video of the Year]]\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://junoawards.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/2016-Gala-Dinners-Awards-Winners-List.pdf |title=2016 JUNO Gala Dinner & Awards Winners |work=JUNO Awards |date=3 April 2016 |accessdate=3 April 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160415101905/http://junoawards.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/2016-Gala-Dinners-Awards-Winners-List.pdf |archivedate=15 April 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Latin American Music Awards]]\n| Favourite Song - Crossover\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/these-are-2016-latin-american-music-awards-nominees-n641241 |title=These are the 2016 Latin American Music Awards Nominees |date=1 September 2016 |publisher=NBC |accessdate=4 September 2016 |author=Latimer, Brian |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160903213259/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/these-are-2016-latin-american-music-awards-nominees-n641241 |archivedate= 3 September 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Los Premios 40 Principales]]\n| International Song of the Year\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://los40.com/especiales/los40-music-awards/2016/nominados/ |title=LOS40 Music Awards 2016: Nominados |language=Spanish |publisher=[[Los 40 Principales]] |date=6 October 2016 |accessdate=11 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011231149/http://los40.com/especiales/los40-music-awards/2016/nominados/ |archivedate=11 October 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[MTV Italian Music Awards]]\n| Best Tormentone (catchphrase)\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://mtvawards.mtv.it/vincitori-2016/|publisher=[[MTV Italy]]|title=VINCITORI 2016\n|date=19 June 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160622135808/http://mtvawards.mtv.it/vincitori-2016/|archivedate=22 June 2016 |accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[MTV Europe Music Award]]\n| [[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Song|Best Song]]\n| {{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |accessdate=7 November 2016 |url=http://www.gossipcop.com/mtv-emas-winners-list-2016-europe-music-awards-categories/ |title=2016 MTV EMAs Winners List! |publisher=[[Gossip Cop]] |date=6 November 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106213052/http://www.gossipcop.com/mtv-emas-winners-list-2016-europe-music-awards-categories/ |archivedate=6 November 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=7| [[MTV Video Music Awards]]\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|last1=Renner Brown |first1=Eric |accessdate=26 July 2016 |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/07/26/mtv-vma-2016-nominations |title=Beyonc\u00e9 and Adele lead 2016 MTV VMA nominations |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=26 July 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160727165723/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/07/26/mtv-vma-2016-nominations |archivedate=27 July 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Female Video|Best Female Video]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Pop Video|Best Pop Video]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Direction|Best Direction]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Art Direction|Best Art Direction]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Awards Japan]]\n| Best International Video\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=MTV Video Music Awards Japan 2016 Winners Announced: Utada Hikaru, Beyonce, Ariana Grande, And More |url=http://www.itechpost.com/articles/46988/20161027/mtv-video-music-awards-japan-2016-winners-announced-utada-hikaru.htm |publisher=MTV |accessdate=7 November 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107155223/http://www.itechpost.com/articles/46988/20161027/mtv-video-music-awards-japan-2016-winners-announced-utada-hikaru.htm |archivedate=7 November 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| Favourite Song of the Year\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\"| <ref>{{cite news|last1=Harrison |first1=Lily |title=Kids' Choice Awards 2016 Nominations Are In: Jennifer Lawrence, Chris Pratt, Anna Kendrick & More Favorites Named |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/736083/kids-choice-awards-2016-nominations-jennifer-lawrence-chris-pratt-anna-kendrick-more-favorites-named |accessdate=3 February 2016 |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=3 February 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160213055425/http://www.eonline.com/news/736083/kids-choice-awards-2016-nominations-jennifer-lawrence-chris-pratt-anna-kendrick-more-favorites-named |archivedate=13 February 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Premios Juventud]]\n| Favourite Hit\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=17 July 2016 |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7438935/premios-juventud-2016-winners |title=Premios Juventud 2016: CNCO, Nicky Jam, Marc Anthony & More Winners |work=Billboard |date=14 July 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716130733/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7438935/premios-juventud-2016-winners |archivedate=16 July 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[Soul Train Music Awards]]\n| [[Soul Train Music Award for Best Song of the Year| Song of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7541060/erykah-badu-2016-soul-train-music-awards-host |title=Erykah Badu Returns to Host the 2016 Soul Train Music Awards as Drake, Beyonce Lead Nominations |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=12 October 2016 |accessdate=13 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161013132726/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7541060/erykah-badu-2016-soul-train-music-awards-host |archivedate=13 October 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n|  [[Soul Train Music Award for The Ashford & Simpson Songwriter's Award|The Ashford & Simpson Songwriter's Award]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n|  [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Music&nbsp;\u2013 Single|Choice Music Single&nbsp;\u2013 Female]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/07/31/teen-choice-awards-2016-winners-list |title=Teen Choice Awards 2016: See the full list of winners |last=Goodman |first=Jessica |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=31 July 2016 |accessdate=1 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803002031/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/07/31/teen-choice-awards-2016-winners-list |archivedate= 3 August 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Radio Disney Music Awards]]\n| Heartbreak&nbsp;\u2013 Best Breakup Song\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=9 March 2016 |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/6898271/radio-disney-music-awards-2016-nominations |title=Taylor Swift & Justin Bieber Lead Radio Disney Music Awards Nominations |work=Billboard |date=4 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306202742/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/6898271/radio-disney-music-awards-2016-nominations |archivedate= 6 March 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"4\" scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| [[APRA Awards (Australia)| Apra Awards]]\n| International Work of the Year\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"IWotYNom 17\">{{cite web|url=http://apraamcos.com.au/awards/2017-awards/apra-music-awards/international-work-of-the-year/ |title=International Work of the Year |publisher=Australasian Performing Right Association (APRA) &#124; Australasian Mechanical Copyright Owners Society (AMCOS) |year=2017 |accessdate=6 April 2017 |df=}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=3|[[Grammy Awards]]\n| [[Grammy Award for Record of the Year|Record of the Year]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=6 December 2016 |url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees |title=59TH ANNUAL GRAMMY AWARDS NOMINEES |work=The Recording Academy |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180131073014/https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/59th-annual-grammy-awards |archivedate= 31 January 2018 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Solo Performance|Best Pop Solo Performance]]\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==Music video==\n{{quote box|quote=\"When I heard the song I saw a story right away. [The video] is highly unoriginal. The lyrics are 'Hello, it's me' and then you see someone picking up a phone. I'm not good at imagining super conceptual videos. I just thought it would be nice to have her walk around the house and make phone calls and end up in a forest, with maybe some flashbacks in it.\"|author=\u2014 Xavier Dolan, behind the concept of the music video<ref name=\"LATimes\" />|align=right|width=30%}}\nThe accompanying music video for the song was directed by Canadian actor and director [[Xavier Dolan]] and released on 22 October 2015, despite the fact the song was released as a single a day later.<ref>{{cite news|title=Adele enlists Xavier Dolan for new music video Hello|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/arts/adele-xavier-dolan-1.3283914||publisher=[[CBC News]]|accessdate=23 October 2015|date=22 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/adele-unveils-25-track-list-plans-hello-video-20151022||last1=Spanos|first1=Brittany|title=Adele Unveils '25' Track List, Plans 'Hello' Video|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=22 October 2015|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref> The concept of the video revolves around a recently broken-up woman calling a younger version of herself.<ref name=\"LATimes\" /> Portions of the video\u2014mostly the finale on the pond and the shot of her opening her eyes in the beginning\u2014were filmed with [[IMAX]] cameras, making it the first music video in IMAX format.<ref>{{cite web|date=23 October 2015|last=Rosen|first=Christopher| url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/10/23/adele-hello-video|title=Adeles's powerful 'Hello' Video Already Made History|accessdate=23 October 2015|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]}}</ref> The video draws inspiration from Dolan's semi-autobiographical debut ''[[I Killed My Mother]]'', which was made when Dolan was barely 20.<ref name=\"LATimes\">{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-adele-hello-video-song-flip-phone-20151023-story.html|title=Director of Adele's 'Hello' video explains its look, theme and, oh yes, flip phone|author=Steven Zeitchik|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=23 October 2015|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref> The video was filmed on a farm in Qu\u00e9bec over 4 days in September 2015.<ref name=\"LATimes\" />\n\nThe video stars American actor [[Tristan Wilds]]. According to Dolan, Adele called him after an unspecified incident of [[police brutality in the United States]], suggesting that a Caucasian male not be cast as her love interest in the video. Dolan elaborated \"She was just like, 'I\u2019m concerned with the reality of the tensions between authorities and the black community, and I want to send a message out there.'\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.vulture.com/2016/12/xavier-dolan-on-his-new-film-critics-and-more.html |title=Xavier Dolan on Blink-182, Bottoming, and Being the World\u2019s Biggest Kate Winslet Fan |publisher=Vulture.com |last=Buchanan |first=Kyle |date= 8 December 2016 |accessdate=17 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/dec/09/adele-black-star-hello-video-police-brutality-xavier-dolan-tristan-wilds |title=Adele cast black star in Hello video to address 'police brutality'  |newspaper=The Guardian |date=10 December 2016 |accessdate=17 February 2017}}</ref> Dolan contacted Wilds via Skype and explained the concept for the video, which Wilds agreed to take part in.<ref name=\"ew.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/10/26/adele-hello-tristan-mack-wilds|title=Tristan Mack Wilds on Adele's Hello |work=Entertainment Weekly's EW.com}}</ref> During the filming, both Adele and Wilds were asked to improvise and \"tap into\" their past relationships in order to convey the correct emotions. Dolan also filmed shots of both Adele and Wilds having conversations and laughing.<ref name=\"ew.com\" /> The [[sepia tone]]d video shows Adele performing the song in a small house and outside in a wooded forest, intercut with scenes of her making a tearful phone call and flashbacks to a past relationship with Wilds' character.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tyrrell|first1=Rebecca|title=The guy in Adele's new music video might look familiar to you|url=http://metro.co.uk/2015/10/23/the-guy-in-adeles-new-music-video-might-look-familiar-to-you-5457876/|accessdate=23 October 2015|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|date=23 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe [[flip phone]] used by Adele in the video was widely commented upon due to being of a [[retro style]]. Dolan replied to the remarks by saying: \"It makes me uncomfortable filming iPhones because I feel like I'm shooting a commercial. Those things: iPhones, laptops, all those elements, to me, they bring me back to reality: That's not what you want. You want to get out of your own life; you want to enter someone else's; you want to travel somewhere; you want to be told a story. I'm realizing maybe I've been more distracting than anything else with that flip phone, but it wasn't intentional!\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = 'Hello' Music Director Explains Why Adele Uses That Flip Phone|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/adele-hello-flip-phone_562bd430e4b0aac0b8fd2030|website = The Huffington Post|accessdate = 10 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe music video for the song broke the previous [[Vevo Record]] by achieving over 27.7&nbsp;million views within a 24-hour period. [[Taylor Swift]] held this record before with her music video for \"[[Bad Blood (Taylor Swift song)|Bad Blood]]\", which amased 20.1 million views in their first 24 hours.<ref name=\"Guardian-Groves\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/oct/27/adeles-hello-beats-taylor-swifts-record-for-most-viewed-video-in-24-hours?CMP=twt_gu|work=The Guardian|date=27 October 2015|first=Nancy|last=Groves| title=Adele's Hello beats Taylor Swift's record for most-viewed video in 24 hours}}</ref> Later, the video continued to break [[Miley Cyrus]]'s \"[[Wrecking Ball (Miley Cyrus song)|Wrecking Ball]]\" Vevo record for the fastest video to reach 100 million views in 5 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://de.eonline.com/news/711235/adele-s-hello-music-video-shatters-miley-cyrus-vevo-record|publisher=E!|date=29 October 2015|first= Francesca|last=Bacardi| title=Adele's \"Hello\" Music Video Shatters Miley Cyrus' Vevo Record}}</ref> The phrase \"Adele hello\" was also the top YouTube search term of Friday and Saturday, and on average the video was getting one million views per hour during the first two days, peaking at 1.6&nbsp;million in a single hour, beating the peak view rate of the trailer for ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'', which peaked at 1.2&nbsp;million views per hour.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/34659073/people-are-playing-adele-one-million-times-an-hour-on-youtube|title=People are playing Adele one million times an hour on YouTube|publisher=BBC}}</ref> The video was parodied in a [[Thanksgiving]]-themed skit on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/11/22/snl-adele-hello-parody-thanksgiving | title=Adele saves awkward Thanksgiving dinner in SNL parody | work=Entertainment Weekly | date=22 November 2015 | accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nAs of February 2020, the video is the [[List of most viewed YouTube videos|22nd most viewed video]] on [[YouTube]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Top 1000 Most Viewed YouTube Videos of All Time|url=https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL11E57E1166929B60 |publisher=YouTube|accessdate=February 24, 2020}}</ref> having earned over 2.6 billion views.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele \u2013 Hello|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YQHsXMglC9A |publisher=YouTube|accessdate=28 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2017/07/05/adeles-hello-hits-2-billion-views-on-youtube/#410fed244c0f|title=Adele's 'Hello' Hits 2 Billion Views On YouTube|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|work=Forbes|access-date=11 October 2017|language=en}}</ref> The video also became the third video on YouTube to reach 10 million likes on 29 May 2016, and has over 15 million likes as of February 2020, ranking it seventh on the [[list of most-liked YouTube videos]]. The six videos to have more likes are \"[[Gangnam Style#Music video|Gangnam Style]]\", \"[[See You Again#Music video|See You Again]]\", \"[[Despacito#Music video|Despacito]]\", \"[[Shape of You]]\", \"[[Faded (Alan Walker song)|Faded]]\" and \"[[Girls Like You]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kworb.net/youtube/topvideos_likes.html|title=Kworb \u2013 Most Liked music videos|publisher=BBC|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\nAdele performed \"Hello\" live for the first time for a [[BBC]] one-hour-long special, ''[[Adele at the BBC]]'', which was recorded on 2 November 2015 and was broadcast on [[BBC One]] on 20 November 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/2d2gP1DTqDZSVP8hGl7ZX4z/exclusive-adele-at-the-bbc-a-first-look-when-adele-met-graham-norton-featuring-hello-live|title=BBC Music \u2013 BBC Music \u2013 *Exclusive* Adele at the BBC, a first look \u2013 When Adele met Graham Norton, featuring Hello (live)|work=BBC}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-34638507|title=Adele to film BBC One special with Graham Norton|work=BBC News}}</ref> She also performed the song at the [[NRJ Music Awards|17th NRJ Music Awards]] on 7 November 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6754075/watch-adele-deliver-powerful-hello-performance-at-frances-nrj-awards|title=Adele Sing 'Hello' at France's NRJ Awards \u2013 Billboard|work=Billboard}}</ref> at [[Radio City Music Hall]] in [[New York City]] on 17 November 2015 as her opening number (''[[Adele Live in New York City]]''), and on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' on 21 November 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/joe-deprospero/adele-at-radio-city-music_b_8591362.html|title=Adele at Radio City Music Hall: A Moment of Beauty at a Time of Unrest|date=18 November 2015|work=The Huffington Post}}</ref> On 23 November 2015, after appearing on ''[[The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]'', Adele recorded the song with Fallon and his house band, ''[[The Roots]]'', playing classroom instruments. The version was broadcast on the show the following night.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/11/25/entertainment/adele-jimmy-fallon-tonight-show-feat/|title=Adele kills it on 'The Tonight Show' with Jimmy Fallon|author=Lisa Respers France, CNN|date=25 November 2015|work=CNN}}</ref>\nOn 13 December 2015 Adele performed \"Hello\" on the ''[[X Factor]]'' live final at [[Wembley Arena|The SSE Arena, Wembley]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Williott|first1=Carl|title=Watch Adele Perform 'Hello' On \u2018X Factor UK\u2019|url=http://www.idolator.com/7617847/adele-hello-x-factor-uk|website=Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on Idolator.com|accessdate=31 January 2016|date=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Cover versions==\n* On 9 November 2015, British singer [[Rita Ora]] delivered her own version of the song by singing it in a self-invented language in the [[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]] studios.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/rita-ora/news/adele-hello-cover-sigma/#9JtCFImi6s8mUX24.97|title=WATCH: Rita Ora Covered Adele's Hello' In Her OWN Language|date=9 November 2015|work=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]]|publisher=[[Global Radio]]|accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref>\n* American singer [[Demi Lovato]] covered \"Hello\" at the 2015 [[KBKS-FM|106.1 KISS FM]] Fall Ball in [[Seattle]] on 14 November 2015. Her rendition of the song was met with high critical acclaim.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/11/demi-lovato-adele-hello-cover|title=Watch Demi Lovato\u2019s Raw and Powerful Cover of Adele\u2019s \"Hello\"|last=Robinson|first=Joanna|date=15 November 2015|work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|publisher=[[Cond\u00e9 Nast]]|accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6762533/watch-demi-lovato-passionately-cover-adele-hello|title=Watch Demi Lovato Passionately Cover Adele's 'Hello'|last=Peters|first=Mitchell|date=15 November 2015|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/demi-lovato-hello_us_5648ea5be4b08cda3489451c|title=Demi Lovato Absolutely Slays Cover Of Adele\u2019s \u2018Hello\u2019|last=Karlin|first=Lily|date=15 November 2015|work=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref> It eventually received a nomination for \"Best Cover Song\" at the [[3rd iHeartRadio Music Awards]].<ref name=\"nominees\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6873866/iheartradio-music-awards-2016-nominees-performers|title=iHeartRadio Music Awards Announce 2016 Nominees, Performers & New Categories|last=Lynch|first=Joe|date=9 February 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref>\n* In December 2015, Washington, D.C.-based [[go-go]] band Backyard Band released a cover version of the song, which has become widely popular in the area since its release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/what-a-viral-cover-of-adeles-hello-means-for-go-go/2016/02/04/40a4bb18-c9cd-11e5-88ff-e2d1b4289c2f_story.html|title=What a viral cover of Adele\u2019s \u2018Hello\u2019 means for go-go|last=Richards|first=Chris|date=4 February 2016|work=[[The Washington Post]]|accessdate=9 May 2016}}</ref>\n*In December 2015, [[Claudio Sanchez]] of American progressive metal band [[Coheed & Cambria]] posted an acoustic cover on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/watch-coheed-and-cambria-cover-adeles-hello-70701/|title=Watch Coheed and Cambria Cover Adele's 'Hello'|first1=Brittany|last1=Spanos|first2=Brittany|last2=Spanos|date=16 December 2015|publisher=}}</ref> The cover was described by critics as \"haunting\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6813525/coheed-and-cambria-claudio-sanchez-adele-hello|title=Watch Coheed and Cambria's Claudio Sanchez' Haunting Version of Adele's 'Hello'|website=Billboard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2015/12/coheed-and-cambrias-claudio-sanchez-performs-haunting-cover-of-adeles-hello/|title=Coheed and Cambria\u2019s Claudio Sanchez performs haunting cover of Adele\u2019s \"Hello\" \u2014 watch|date=16 December 2015|publisher=}}</ref>\n* During New Year's Eve 2015, Canadian singer [[Celine Dion]] put her own spin on \"Hello\" at her [[Celine (residency show)|residency show]] in [[Las Vegas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6828871/celine-dion-covers-adele-hello|title=Watch Celine Dion's Perfect Cover of Adele's 'Hello'|last=Strecker|first=Erin|date=1 January 2016|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Media usage==\n{{unreferenced section|date=September 2017}}\nThe song was mentioned in the season 6 premier episode of ''[[2 Broke Girls]].'' \"Hello\" is also referenced in the [[Lady Leshurr]] single \"Queen's Speech 5\" and was also sampled in [[Stitches (rapper)|Stitches]]' single \"One Million Dimes\".\n\n==Credits and personnel==\n'''Personnel'''<ref name=\"Target version booklet\">{{Cite AV media notes |title=25 |others=[[Adele]] |year=2015 |url=http://www.target.com/p/adele-25-target-exclusive/-/A-50281802 |first=Adele |last=Adkins |pages=12\u201313 |type=Booklet |publisher=[[XL Recordings]] |id=88875176782 |location=London, England, U.K. |accessdate=26 November 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427051216/http://www.target.com/p/adele-25-target-exclusive/-/A-50281802 |archivedate=27 April 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n* [[Singing|Vocals]], [[drums]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Adele]]\n* [[Songwriter|Songwriting]]&nbsp;\u2013 Adele Adkins, [[Greg Kurstin]]\n* [[Record producer|Production]], [[piano]], [[Bass guitar|bass]], [[drums]], [[Bass guitar|guitar]], [[electronic keyboard]]&nbsp;\u2013 Greg Kurstin\n* [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|Mixing]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Tom Elmhirst]]\n* [[Audio engineering|Engineering]]&nbsp;\u2013 Alex Pasco, Greg Kurstin, Julian Burg, Liam Nolan\n* [[Audio mastering|Mastering]]&nbsp;\u2013 Randy Merrill, [[Tom Coyne (music engineer)|Tom Coyne]]\n* Additional instruments&nbsp;\u2013 [[Emile Haynie]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2015\u201316)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|1|artist=Adele|song=Hello|rowheader=true|accessdate=31 October 2015}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|1|artist=Adele|song=Hello|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 November 2015}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|1|artist=Adele|song=Hello|rowheader=true|accessdate=31 October 2015}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|1|artist=Adele|song=Hello|rowheader=true|accessdate=31 October 2015}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Brazil ([[Brasil Hot 100 Airplay|''Billboard'' Brasil Hot 100]])<ref name=brabill>{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com.br/rankings |title=Hot 100 Billboard Brasil&nbsp;\u2013 weekly |work=[[Billboard Brasil]] |date=26 January 2016 |accessdate=27 January 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160716161516/http://billboard.com.br/rankings |archivedate=16 July 2016  }}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada|1|artist=Adele|rowheader=true|accessdate=3 November 2015}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canada [[Adult contemporary music|AC]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite web|title=Chart Search|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5b0%5d=ts_chart_artistname%3AAdele&f%5b1%5d=itm_field_chart_id%3A1237&f%5b2%5d=ss_bb_type%3Achart_item&type=2&artist=Adele|publisher=[[Billboard charts|Billboard]] [[Canada AC]] for Adele|accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canada [[CHR/Top 40]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite web|titl